e. We must then reenvision contemporary politics as operating at the level of the feeling body, so we can better understand the physiological and epistemological conditions affirming our cultural status quo and contestatory strategies for emancipation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAestheticsxPsychological aspects. 0aAffect (Psychology) 0aAffect (Psychology). 0aCapitalism. 0aGlobalizationxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Critical Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/rebe1705240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231540902423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231540902.jpg  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles